Arthur Dalby Martin (9 November 1888 – 12 July 1958) was an English cricketer.  Martin's batting and bowling styles are unknown.  He was born at Hackney, London.
Martin made three first-class appearances for Essex against Somerset in 1920 and Northamptonshire and Middlesex in 1921.  He had three batting innings, making a duck in each.  He also took a total of 5 wickets in these matches, which came at an average of 42.00, with best figures of 3/43.He died on 12 July 1958 at Northwood, Middlesex.
